    "updated_at": "2015-01-16T22:25:43Z",
    "body": "Which would require major changes throughout rustc, as I understand it.\n\nWe could instead have a global flag that tells the existing panic handler what context rustc was in at the time of panic, e.g. built-in code or the name of a plugin.  We'd print this in the message and maybe use it to be more equivocal about whether to report the bug (kind of like Linux's taint bits).\n",
